{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Log entries with the same trace ID are grouped together regardless of which microservice emitted them.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure risk is at the boundary between ingestion/parsing and correlation modules (field mapping, normalization, merge logic across service sources). A unit test of only the grouping function can miss real mismatches in how different service records are decoded and handed off.","test_description":"Run an integration test that feeds mixed JSON log batches from at least 3 simulated services into the real ingest + correlate pipeline, then assert all records sharing a trace ID end up in one correlated request group with no cross-trace contamination.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The timeline view orders entries by timestamp, correctly handling clock skew of up to 500ms between services.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Correctness depends on interaction between timestamp parsing, skew-tolerance logic, and timeline assembly. Pure unit tests of sorting alone can miss failures where skew metadata or service-origin context is lost between modules.","test_description":"Run an integration test through real timeline-building modules with synthetic multi-service traces containing controlled ±500ms skew and near-boundary events; assert output order matches expected causal timeline and remains stable at the 500ms threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A latency spike (p99 above 3x the baseline) is detected and flagged in the anomaly report.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The critical failure boundary is wiring percentile computation + baseline windowing + anomaly report emission. A unit test of p99 math may pass while real report thresholds or metric routing are wrong.","test_description":"Run an integration test that ingests a baseline period and then a spike period where p99 exceeds 3x baseline; assert anomaly report contains a latency-spike flag with the correct metric and window context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Malformed JSON log entries are skipped without crashing the pipeline, and the count of skipped entries is reported.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is often in parser-to-pipeline error propagation and counters, not just JSON parse exceptions. In-process mocks can hide crashes in batch/stream handling paths and miscounted skip metrics.","test_description":"Run an integration test with a mixed stream of valid and malformed JSON records through the real ingest pipeline; assert process continues, valid records are processed, malformed ones are skipped, and skipped-entry count matches exact malformed input count.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.13,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The tool handles a burst of 10,000 log entries per second without dropping entries or falling behind.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a runtime throughput/backpressure behavior that depends on real scheduler timing, queue behavior, memory pressure, and I/O characteristics. Mocked or purely in-process tests can pass while production-like load drops entries or accumulates lag.","test_description":"Run a system load test that drives the deployed binary/service with a sustained 10k entries/sec burst using real process boundaries and transport path; measure ingest lag and end-to-end counts, asserting zero drops and bounded backlog growth during and after burst.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
